
[1]frantic

   FRAN'TIC, a. [L. phreneticus; Gr. from delirium or raving, from mind,
   the radical sense of which is to rush, to drive forward.]

   1. Mad; raving; furious; outrageous; wild and disorderly; distracted;
   as a frantic person; frantic with fear or grief.

   2. Characterized by violence, fury and disorder; noisy; mad; wild;
   irregular; as the frantic rites of Bacchus.
